programme.title: 2018 FIFA World Cup
programme.desc: Coverage of the opening ceremony, followed by Russia v Saudi Arabia (Kick-off 4.00pm). Darragh Maloney is joined by Eamon Dunphy and Liam Brady as the prestigious tournament gets under way with this Group A encounter at Luzhniki Stadium in Moscow. This is only Russia's third appearance in a World Cup this century after failing to qualify for the tournaments in 2006 and 2010. Their last effort in 2014 saw them fail to get out of the group stage, drawing two games and losing one, but as hosts they'll be expecting to go much further this time around. This afternoon will see them face Saudi Arabia for the first time since October 1993, when they lost 4-2 in Riyadh in a friendly match. Juan Antonio Pizzi's side are playing in only their fifth World Cup and will be looking to at least match their previous best finish, which saw them reach the last 16 at the 1994 tournament in the USA. With commentary by George Hamilton and Ronnie Whelan(c)

programme.desc: Liam Neeson stars as former CIA operative Bryan Mills, who's desperate to track down his kidnapped daughter in Pierre Morel's Luc Besson-produced action-thriller. Mills' life hasn't panned out well; his dedication to the CIA wrecked his marriage and made him neglect his daughter Kim. Now, retired from the Agency, he wants to make things up to Kim. But to do so, he has to contend with his ex-wife's animosity and Kim's new step-father's wealth. So when he has an opportunity to advance Kim's pop star ambitions he jumps at the chance, even if that means her and a friend crossing the Atlantic to brave 'the dangers of Europe'. As things turn out, he has a point: in Paris, the two girls are kidnapped by vicious Eastern European sex traffickers. As they are being abducted, Bryan tells one of the baddies, via Kim's mobile phone: 'I will look for you, I will find you, and I will kill you'. He subsequently does his best to make good on his promise, using all the violent tricks of the trade his time at the CIA taught him(n)

programme.desc: Hoping for one last shot at Wimbledon glory, a fading British tennis star courts a promising American player on the circuit, and she helps him regain his focus and climb to the top of the rankings. Former tennis greats John McEnroe and Chris Evert have cameos(n)

programme.title: Miami Vice
programme.desc: Based on Michael Mann's groundbreaking eighties series, which captured the world of Miami vice cops with a unique aesthetic that coupled sleekness and grittiness, the film explores the alluring and dangerous whirlwind of deep undercover police work. In the roles of Sonny Crockett and Ricardo Tubbs, Colin Farrell and Jamie Foxx go where their badges don't count as they are asked to investigate the murder of two federal agents. In the process they get pulled into an underworld of drug trafficking from which it may be too difficult to make it back to reality(n)

programme.title: Devil
programme.desc: Chris Messina headlines this thriller produced by M. Night Shyamalan about a group of strangers who are trapped in an elevator together and come to the realization that one of them is the Devil. Directed by John Erick Dowdle(n)

programme.title: X-Men
programme.desc: (2000) Bryan Singer's fantasy film is set on a parallel Earth where humans reluctantly live alongside mutants, those with genetic "defects" that give them superhuman powers. The mutants are gathered into two camps. Those at Professor Charles Xavier's (Patrick Stewart) school are taught to curb their powers and use them for good, while his opposite number, Magneto (Ian McKellen), believes that humans want to destroy them and is assembling a force to win the day by turning the world's leaders into mutants. The film concentrates on Wolverine and Rogue (Hugh Jackman, Anna Paquin), who side with Xavier as the two factions launch into climactic battle. Edited for language and violence ; HD Wide(n)

programme.title: Wasted! The Story of Food Waste
programme.desc: Renowned chefs discuss the economic and environmental costs of global food waste, and explore solutions that involve educating consumers and food suppliers. This documentary also includes interviews with industry experts, who talk about how to change the fact that one-third of all food produced on the planet is thrown away uneaten(n)

programme.title: The Neighbor
programme.desc: Mike, a middle-aged man stuck in a loveless marriage, sees his life take a dramatic turn when married couple Jenna and Scott move in next door. Mike develops an infatuation with Jenna, and soon becomes suspicious that Scott is abusing her(n)

programme.title: Tommy Boy
programme.desc: Tommy Callaham Jr. nunca ha sido un estudiante modelo, más bien un auténtico desastre más interesado en las juergas universitarias que en los libros. Después de siete años de retraso consigue graduarse y debe regresar a Ohio, donde trabajará en el negocio familiar. Al llegar se encuentra con una serie de cambios, entre ellos la nueva y explosiva mujer de su padre(n)
